               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1397" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1397" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1397" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1397" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ROBINSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am errand-boy to Mr. William Golding, a chemist, in Upper Albany-street, Regent's Park—about half-past ten o'clock in the morn<lb></lb>ing on the 5th of April, the prisoner came and desired my master to send a black draught and a pill, and asked how long—it would be before he sent it—my master said half an hour—the prisoner said, "Before that"—my master said he would send it as soon as he could, and he told him to send change for a half sovereign—my master gave me the draught and pill, and 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I met the prisoner—he took the things and the change, and gave me what I supposed was a half-sovereign, but I looked and saw the feathers on the re<lb></lb>verse side—I ran after him, and called "Stop thief"—the policeman caught</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080214"></xptr>
               <p>him—I have not been to No. 4, Augusta-square, where the prisoner ordered the things to go to.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Are you sure I came to the shop and ordered them? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I know you by your dress—I lost sight of you, but got sight of you again in Hampstead-road.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1398" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1398" type="surname" value="JOLLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1398" type="given" value="ALFRED JOSEPH"></interp>ALFRED JOSEPH JOLLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to Mr. Mortlock in Oxford-street. I was in Hampstead-road on Good Friday—the prisoner passed me, and as he passed he threw a white paper over a garden wall—I got over and got it—there was nine shillings and a 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece in it—I am sure he threw it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1399" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1399" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1399" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CLARK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I took the prisoner, and have this medal from Robinson—I have been to No. 4, Augusta-square—the prisoner it not known there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I gave the boy a good half-sovereign, and he was showing it about to several persons before he gave it to the officer.</p>
